text.tspan: Arcane colour script (which later became a colour a second) was one of the visualizations I had my heart set on creating. The goal
was to create something similar to animated movies colour scripts Pixar and Disney does, however researching the tools for that the
closest I found was a python script that extract dominate colours from an images folder. Having never worked with Python before, I
reach for Harold for help. Screenshots include me converting the episodes into a 1 frame per second small sized images, my
attempts at Python, and the demo pages for the tools I am trying to use in my script.
a colour a second: data prep
